From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: MedyMa build <build@bpi-r4>
Date: Mon, 01 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: mt7988a-bananapi-bpi-r4: fix LEDs for mtwifi/BE14000

Fix the GPIO LED definitions for the BPI-R4 H2 front-panel header:

G (green, GPIO 79): Replace 'default-state = "on"' with an explicit
  'linux,default-trigger = "default-on"' so the LED stays lit even when
  the mtwifi vendor driver re-initialises GPIOs after the leds-gpio driver.

B (blue, GPIO 63): Change from LED_FUNCTION_WPS (requires a WPS event to
  activate) to LED_FUNCTION_INDICATOR with a 'heartbeat' trigger so it
  blinks as a visible system-alive indicator regardless of WiFi state.
  When CONFIG_MTK_WIFI7_LED_CONTROL_SUPPORT is active the driver will later
  take over GPIO 63 for WiFi activity; the heartbeat default keeps the LED
  useful on first boot before WiFi initialises.

SSD (GPIO 10): Add disk-activity LED node.  GPIO 10 is derived from the
  BPI-R4-Main V1.1 schematic H2 connector -- verify against your board
  revision before shipping.  The disk-activity trigger fires on any
  block-layer I/O (NVMe or eMMC).
---
 .../boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988a-bananapi-bpi-r4.dtsi | 15 +++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/target/linux/mediatek/files-6.6/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988a-bananapi-bpi-r4.dtsi b/target/linux/mediatek/files-6.6/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988a-bananapi-bpi-r4.dtsi
--- a/target/linux/mediatek/files-6.6/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988a-bananapi-bpi-r4.dtsi
+++ b/target/linux/mediatek/files-6.6/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988a-bananapi-bpi-r4.dtsi
@@ -64,14 +64,22 @@
 		led_green: led-green {
 			function = LED_FUNCTION_STATUS;
 			color = <LED_COLOR_ID_GREEN>;
 			gpios = <&pio 79 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;
-			default-state = "on";
+			linux,default-trigger = "default-on";
 		};

 		led_blue: led-blue {
-			function = LED_FUNCTION_WPS;
+			function = LED_FUNCTION_INDICATOR;
 			color = <LED_COLOR_ID_BLUE>;
 			gpios = <&pio 63 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;
-			default-state = "off";
+			linux,default-trigger = "heartbeat";
+		};
+
+		led_ssd: led-ssd {
+			label = "green:ssd";
+			function = LED_FUNCTION_DISK;
+			color = <LED_COLOR_ID_GREEN>;
+			gpios = <&pio 10 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;
+			linux,default-trigger = "disk-activity";
 		};
 	};
